    <string name="about_indonesia_body">Indonesia is the world\'s largest archipelago, with more than 17,000 islands stretching from Sabang to Merauke across 5,100 kilometers. Home to more than 270 million people, over 1,300 ethnic groups, and hundreds of local languages, Indonesia is one of the most culturally diverse places on earth.\n\nIts landscapes are extraordinary: from the underwater beauty of Raja Ampat and the rice terraces of Ubud to Borobudur Temple and Komodo National Park. Indonesia is also one of the world\'s richest megadiverse countries, home to remarkable plant, mammal, and bird species.\n\nWith WisataKita, explore this beauty one destination at a time.</string>
